{
  "texts": [
    "The threshold of 3.5 is determined from the local minimum in the amplitudeoccurrence distribution in Fig. 6.",
    "Some events corresponding to amplitudes ≤ 3.5 are obscured by points corresponding to larger-amplitude events and/or known seismicity labels.",
    "where events that have a broad range of amplitudes have similar energies.",
    "Stick-slip waveforms on the WIS can vary based on rupture location and tide (Pratt et al., 2014, their Fig. 5).",
    "Therefore, the different types of stick-slip events can be attributed to those differences."
  ]
}